create_issue "Decode diagnostic events into human-readable output" "The \`events\` subcommand should decode base64 XDR DiagnosticEvents into plain English.\n\n**Background:** In the hintents simulator, \`categorize_events\` maps \`ContractEventType\` variants to lowercase strings: Contract → \"contract\", System → \"system\", Diagnostic → \"diagnostic\". The \`in_successful_contract_call\` field must be the negation of \`failed_call\`.\n\n**Expected output:**\n\`\`\`\nEvent #1\n  Type:     diagnostic\n  Contract: GABC...\n  Topics:   [\"transfer\"]\n  Data:     \"100\"\n\`\`\`\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- Correctly decodes sample XDR\n- \`event_type\` is lowercase string\n- \`in_successful_contract_call == !failed_call\`\n- Graceful error on malformed input\n- Integration test with known input/output pair\n\n**PR requirements:**\n- Run \`cargo fmt\` and \`cargo clippy\` before submitting\n- Include test named \`test_in_successful_contract_call_is_negation_of_failed_call\`" "help wanted,diagnostics,soroban"
create_issue "Add JSON output mode to simulate subcommand" "Add \`--json\` flag for structured JSON output.\n\n**Expected output:**\n\`\`\`json\n{\"success\": true, \"cpu_instructions\": 504211, \"memory_bytes\": 1024, \"events\": []}\n\`\`\`\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- \`--json\` produces valid JSON\n- Plain text unchanged without flag\n- Both modes tested\n\n**PR requirements:**\n- Run \`cargo fmt\` and \`cargo clippy\` before submitting" "help wanted,cli,output"
create_issue "Load ledger snapshot from JSON file" "Accept \`--ledger snapshot.json\` to populate host storage before simulation.\n\n**Format:**\n\`\`\`json\n{\"entries\": [{\"key\": \"<base64-xdr-LedgerKey>\", \"value\": \"<base64-xdr-LedgerEntry>\"}]}\n\`\`\`\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- Entries correctly loaded before execution\n- Clear errors for malformed entries\n- Test with at least one entry\n\n**PR requirements:**\n- Run \`cargo fmt\` and \`cargo clippy\` before submitting" "help wanted,ledger,soroban"
create_issue "Implement contract_id_to_hex helper function" "Implement \`contract_id_to_hex(id: &Hash) -> String\` converting raw contract hash to hex string for display.\n\n**Function signature:**\n\`\`\`rust\nfn contract_id_to_hex(id: &Hash) -> String {\n    hex::encode(&id.0 .0[..])\n}\n\`\`\`\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- Returns correct hex encoding\n- Used in event display output\n- Unit tests with known inputs\n\n**PR requirements:**\n- Run \`cargo fmt\` and \`cargo clippy\` before submitting" "help wanted,soroban"
create_issue "Implement scval_to_xdr_base64 helper function" "Implement \`scval_to_xdr_base64(val: &ScVal) -> String\` serializing ScVal to base64-encoded XDR.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- Correctly encodes Int, String, Symbol ScVal types\n- Round-trip test (encode then decode equals original)\n- Unit tests with known inputs\n\n**PR requirements:**\n- Run \`cargo fmt\` and \`cargo clippy\` before submitting" "help wanted,soroban"
create_issue "Add WASM validation step before simulation" "Before running simulation, validate the WASM binary for Soroban compatibility.\n\n**Background:** Use \`vm::enforce_soroban_compatibility(&wasm_bytes)\` which returns \`Err\` for non-compliant contracts. If it returns \`Err(e)\`, return \`send_error(format!(\"Strict VM enforcement failed: {}\", e))\`.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- Float contracts rejected with clear message\n- SIMD contracts rejected\n- Valid contracts pass through\n- Test: \`test_enforce_soroban_compatibility_rejects_floats\`\n\n**PR requirements:**\n- Run \`cargo fmt\` and \`cargo clippy\` before submitting" "help wanted,wasm"
create_issue "Implement batch simulation from JSON manifest" "Add \`simulate --batch manifest.json\` to run multiple calls in sequence.\n\n**Format:**\n\`\`\`json\n[{\"function\": \"transfer\", \"args\": [\"GABC\", \"GXYZ\", \"100\"]}]\n\`\`\`\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- All invocations run in order\n- Results shown as table\n- One failure does not stop batch\n\n**PR requirements:**\n- Run \`cargo fmt\` and \`cargo clippy\` before submitting" "help wanted,cli"
create_issue "Add --assert-return flag to validate return value" "Allow \`--assert-return \"100\"\` to fail if return value doesn't match.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- Exit 0 when return matches assertion\n- Exit 1 when it does not match\n- Useful in CI scripts\n\n**PR requirements:**\n- Run \`cargo fmt\` and \`cargo clippy\` before submitting" "help wanted,testing"
create_issue "Format ScVal return values as human-readable strings" "Decode return values and display in human-readable format.\n\n**Examples:**\n- \`ScVal::I64(42)\` → \`42 (i64)\`\n- \`ScVal::Symbol(\"transfer\")\` → \`\"transfer\" (symbol)\`\n- \`ScVal::Void\` → \`void\`\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- All common ScVal variants handled\n- Fallback to hex for unknown types\n- Unit tests for each variant\n\n**PR requirements:**\n- Run \`cargo fmt\` and \`cargo clippy\` before submitting" "help wanted,output,soroban"
create_issue "Add --ledger-sequence flag to set simulated ledger sequence" "Allow \`--ledger-sequence 1234567\` to set the ledger sequence number in the simulation context.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- Sequence set on host before execution\n- Contracts reading ledger sequence reflect value\n- Test verifies accessibility\n\n**PR requirements:**\n- Run \`cargo fmt\` and \`cargo clippy\` before submitting" "help wanted,ledger"

