create_issue "Implement extract_wasm_instruction for diagnostic output" "Extract the WASM instruction name from diagnostic event data when the topic is \`tick\` or \`budget\`.\n\n**Background:** Topics containing \`\\\"tick\\\"\`, \`tick\`, \`\\\"budget\\\"\`, or \`budget\` indicate budget-related events. The data field may contain \`Instruction: i32.add\` — extract \`i32.add\`.\n\n**Function signature:**\n\`\`\`rust\nfn extract_wasm_instruction(topics: &[String], data: &str) -> Option<String>\n\`\`\`\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- Correctly extracts instruction from \`Instruction: i32.add\` pattern\n- Returns None for non-budget topics\n- Tests: \`test_extract_wasm_instruction\`\n\n**PR requirements:**\n- Run \`cargo fmt\` and \`cargo clippy\` before submitting" "help wanted,wasm,diagnostics"
create_issue "Add --fee-limit flag to cap transaction fee" "Allow \`--fee-limit 10000\` to set maximum fee in stroops.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- Fee limit passed to simulation\n- Estimated fee reported\n- Warning if estimated exceeds limit\n\n**PR requirements:**\n- Run \`cargo fmt\` and \`cargo clippy\` before submitting" "help wanted,cli"
create_issue "Implement decode_error for human-readable VM errors" "Map raw Soroban/WASM error strings to clear English descriptions.\n\n**Examples:**\n- \`wasm trap: out of bounds\` → \`VM Trap: Out of Bounds Access (VM Trap: Out of bounds memory access — the contract read or wrote outside its allocated memory region.)\`\n- \`integer overflow\` → \`VM Trap: Integer Overflow — arithmetic exceeded integer bounds.\`\n- \`stack overflow\` → \`VM Trap: Stack Overflow — the contract exceeded the maximum call-stack depth.\`\n- \`auth\` or \`unauthorized\` → \`Authorization failure — a required signer or policy check was not satisfied.\`\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- All common VM trap types handled\n- Fallback returns raw message unchanged\n- Tests: \`test_decode_vm_traps\`, \`test_decode_unreachable\`\n\n**PR requirements:**\n- Run \`cargo fmt\` and \`cargo clippy\` before submitting" "help wanted,diagnostics"
create_issue "Add --resource-calibration flag to tune resource limits" "Allow passing a JSON resource calibration config to tune CPU and memory limits.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- JSON config parsed and applied to host\n- Invalid config produces clear error\n- Documented with example\n\n**PR requirements:**\n- Run \`cargo fmt\` and \`cargo clippy\` before submitting" "help wanted,cli,soroban"
create_issue "Implement extract_missing_key_id for storage errors" "Extract ledger key ID from HostError strings.\n\n**Background:** Soroban host errors for missing storage entries contain the LedgerKey in debug output:\n\`\`\`\nHostError: ... storage get ... LedgerKey(ContractData(...))\nkey = \"GABC.../some_key\"\n\`\`\`\n\n**Patterns to handle:**\n1. \`LedgerKey(...)\` — soroban debug output\n2. \`key = \"...\"\` — explicit key label\n3. \`ContractData(...)\` — without LedgerKey wrapper\n\n**Function signature:**\n\`\`\`rust\nfn extract_missing_key_id(raw: &str) -> Option<String>\n\`\`\`\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- All three patterns handled\n- Returns None when no key found\n- Tests: \`test_missing_ledger_entry_includes_key_id\`, \`test_extract_missing_key_id_explicit_key_label\`, \`test_missing_ledger_entry_contract_data_pattern\`\n\n**PR requirements:**\n- Run \`cargo fmt\` and \`cargo clippy\` before submitting" "help wanted,diagnostics,soroban"
create_issue "Add --auth flag to provide authorisation entries" "Allow \`--auth auth.json\` to provide base64 XDR auth entries.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- Auth entries loaded and passed to host\n- Test with contract requiring auth\n- Clear error if malformed\n\n**PR requirements:**\n- Run \`cargo fmt\` and \`cargo clippy\` before submitting" "help wanted,cli,soroban"
create_issue "Generate LCOV coverage report from simulation" "Write LCOV report showing which WASM functions were invoked.\n\n**Background:** Use \`CoverageTracker\` which has \`invoked_functions: HashMap<String, u64>\`. Generate report with \`generate_lcov_report(coverage: &CoverageTracker, wasm_path: &str) -> String\`.\n\n**LCOV format:**\n\`\`\`\nSF:/path/to/contract.wasm\nFN:1,InvokeContract::\"transfer\"\"\nFNDA:3,InvokeContract::\"transfer\"\"\nFNF:2\nFNH:2\nend_of_record\n\`\`\`\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- LCOV file written to \`--coverage-output\` path\n- Test: \`test_generate_lcov_report_contains_function_hits\`\n\n**PR requirements:**\n- Run \`cargo fmt\` and \`cargo clippy\` before submitting" "help wanted,testing"
create_issue "Add --footprint flag to display transaction footprint" "Display read/write footprint after simulation.\n\n**Expected output:**\n\`\`\`\nFootprint:\n  Read:  ContractData(GABC..., \"balance\")\n  Write: ContractData(GABC..., \"balance\")\n\`\`\`\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- Footprint displayed after simulation\n- Shown in JSON when \`--json\` set\n- Test with contract that reads and writes\n\n**PR requirements:**\n- Run \`cargo fmt\` and \`cargo clippy\` before submitting" "help wanted,soroban"
create_issue "Add --print-auth flag to display required auth entries" "Display auth entries required to submit the transaction.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- Auth entries printed in base64 XDR\n- Decoded when \`--verbose\` is set\n- Test with contract requiring auth\n\n**PR requirements:**\n- Run \`cargo fmt\` and \`cargo clippy\` before submitting" "help wanted,soroban"
create_issue "Add --source-account flag to set transaction source" "Allow \`--source-account GABC...\` to set source account.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- Source account set on context\n- Validated as Stellar account ID\n- Test verifies accessibility\n\n**PR requirements:**\n- Run \`cargo fmt\` and \`cargo clippy\` before submitting" "help wanted,cli"

