create_issue "Implement categorize_events function" "Implement function categorising HostEvents into CategorizedEvents with human-readable type labels.\n\n**Background:** This was a real conflict in the hintents codebase. \`ContractEventType::Contract\` → \`\"contract\"\`, \`ContractEventType::System\` → \`\"system\"\`, \`ContractEventType::Diagnostic\` → \`\"diagnostic\"\`. The \`in_successful_contract_call\` field must always equal \`!event.failed_call\`.\n\n**Struct:**\n\`\`\`rust\nstruct CategorizedEvent {\n    category: String,\n    event: DiagnosticEvent,\n}\n\`\`\`\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- All three event types categorised correctly\n- \`event_type\` field is lowercase string\n- \`in_successful_contract_call == !failed_call\` always\n- Tests: \`test_in_successful_contract_call_is_negation_of_failed_call\`, \`test_categorize_events_type_labels\`\n\n**PR requirements:**\n- Run \`cargo fmt\` and \`cargo clippy\` before submitting" "help wanted,diagnostics,soroban"
